{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView","doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Lays out all visible lines"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@discardableResult"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"layoutLines","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"in"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"rect"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"NSRect","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh","text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TextLine","identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLine"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"text":"ID","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview Of The Layout Routine","anchor":"Overview-Of-The-Layout-Routine","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The basic premise of this method is that it loops over all lines in the given rect (defaults to the visible","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rect), checks if the line needs a layout calculation, and performs layout on the line if it does."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The thing that makes this layout method so fast is the second point, checking if a line needs layout. To"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"determine if a line needs a layout pass, the layout manager can check three things:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Was the line laid out under the assumption of a different maximum layout width?"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For instance, if a line was previously broken by the line wrapping setting, it won’t need to wrap once the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"line wrapping is disabled. This will detect that, and cause the lines to be recalculated.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"2","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Was the line previously not visible? This is determined by keeping a set of visible line IDs. If the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"line does not appear in that set, we can assume it was previously off screen and may need layout.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"text":" Was the line entirely laid out? We break up lines into line fragments. When we do layout, we determine","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all line fragments but don’t necessarily place them all in the view. This checks if all line fragments have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"been placed in the view. If not, we need to place them."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once it has been determined that a line needs layout, we perform layout by recalculating it’s line fragments,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"removing all old line fragment views, and creating new ones for the line.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Laziness","level":2,"text":"Laziness","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the end of the layout pass, we clean up any old lines by updating the set of visible line IDs and fragment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"IDs. Any IDs that no longer appear in those sets are removed to save resources. This facilitates the text view’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ability to only render text that is visible and saves tons of resources (similar to the lazy loading of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"collection or table views).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The other important lazy attribute is the line iteration. Line iteration is done lazily. As we iterate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"through lines and potentially update their heights, the next line is only queried for ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"after"}]},{"text":" the updates are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"finished.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Reentry","text":"Reentry"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An important thing to note is that this method cannot be reentered. If a layout pass has begun while a layout","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"pass is already ongoing, internal data structures will be broken. In debug builds, this is checked with a simple"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"boolean and assertion."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To help ensure this property, all view modifications are performed within a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CATransaction","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This guarantees"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that macOS calls ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"layout"},{"text":" on any related views only after we’ve finished inserting and removing line fragment","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views. Otherwise, inserting a line fragment view could trigger a layout pass prematurely and cause this method","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to re-enter."}]},{"name":"Warning","type":"aside","style":"warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is probably not what you’re looking for. If you need to invalidate layout, or update lines, this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is not the way to do so. This should only be called when macOS performs layout.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"layoutLines"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"in","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSRect","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh","text":"Set"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"TextLine","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa","text":"ID","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"CodeEditTextView","modules":[{"name":"CodeEditTextView"}],"role":"symbol","title":"layoutLines(in:)","externalID":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C13LayoutManagerC11layoutLines2inShy10Foundation4UUIDVGSo6CGRectVSg_tF","roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager\/layoutlines(in:)"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager\/layoutLines(in:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","title":"CodeEditTextView","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview","abstract":[{"text":"A text editor designed to edit code documents.","type":"text"}]},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLayoutManager":{"abstract":[{"text":"The text layout manager manages laying out lines in a code document.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"TextLayoutManager","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TextLayoutManager"}],"url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager","identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TextLayoutManager"}]},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLayoutManager/layoutLines(in:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLayoutManager\/layoutLines(in:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"layoutLines"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"in","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSRect","text":"NSRect"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sh","text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC","text":"TextLine","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:16CodeEditTextView0C4LineC2IDa","text":"ID"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"title":"layoutLines(in:)","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textlayoutmanager\/layoutlines(in:)","abstract":[{"text":"Lays out all visible lines","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView/documentation/CodeEditTextView/TextLine":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeedittextview.CodeEditTextView\/documentation\/CodeEditTextView\/TextLine","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Represents a displayable line of text."}],"title":"TextLine","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TextLine","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/codeedittextview\/textline","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TextLine","kind":"identifier"}]}}}